s. Harder and denser than ginger - best grated rather than chopped. Thrives in warm humid conditions. Grows well in USDA zones 8-11, suitable for humid subtropical climates. Requires partial shade and consistent moisture. Medicinal uses in traditional Asian medicine.", "availability": "Asian plant nurseries, Baker Creek Heirloom Seeds, specialty suppliers, can propagate from store-bought rhizomes"}, {"name": "Lesser Galangal (Alpinia officinarum)", "slug": "lesser-galangal-alpinia-officinarum", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 17, "origin": "Native to China and Southeast Asia", "traits": "Smaller stature than greater galangal (90cm tall), reddish-brown rhizomes", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate yield, slower growing (best harvested after 2 years)", "growing_notes": "Can grow in humid subtropical climates but slower growing than greater galangal. Used extensively in traditional Chinese medicine. Historical use in European medieval cooking. Requires partial shade and well-drained soil. More cold-tolerant than greater galangal. Good for medicinal herb gardens. Less common in culinary use but valued for health properties.", "availability": "Specialty medicinal herb nurseries, Chinese herb suppliers, limited availability"}, {"name": "Myoga Ginger (Zingiber mioga)", "slug": "myoga-ginger-zingiber-mioga", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 18, "origin": "Native to Japan and East Asia", "traits": "Flowers and young shoots emerge from soil, perennial with spreading rhizomes", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good production of flower buds and shoots", "growing_notes": "Suitable for Humid subtropical climate with adequate shade. Prefers partial shade and moist soil. in humid subtropical climates, grow in shaded areas with consistent moisture. Unique ginger that''s harvested for flowers rather than roots. Prized in Japanese cuisine as a garnish. Can spread to f